  "dateModified": "2026-03-06",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "A narrative essay is an essay that uses storytelling as its primary method of developing an idea. The essay\u0026rsquo;s argument emerges from the story rather than being stated as a thesis and defended with evidence — the narrative is the evidence, and the reader draws the conclusion from the experience of reading it.\nThe narrative essay borrows techniques from fiction — scene construction, dialogue, pacing, concrete detail — but deploys them in service of essayistic thinking. The difference from a short story is intent: a story creates an experience; a narrative essay uses an experience to think through a question.\n",
